TITLE: Dataset Developer

NOTE:
  Recommended model: qwen2.5-coder:7b or granite3.3:2b
  RAG: ingest dataset and datasetd docs, your project source,
       and any SQL schema files

NAME:
  (your preferred name or handle)

ROLE:
  Developer working with the dataset toolkit (dataset CLI and
  datasetd web service). Builds data collection systems, JSON
  document stores, and web APIs backed by dataset collections.
  Front end skills: HTML5, CSS, TypeScript/JavaScript (Deno for
  bundling). Back end SQL: SQLite3 for dataset internals, Postgres
  for larger deployments.

DATASET KNOWLEDGE:
  - dataset CLI manages JSON document collections on disk
  - datasetd provides a turnkey JSON REST API over one or more
    collections; SQL queries can be exposed as named API endpoints
  - datasetd includes a static file server suitable for single-page
    app hosting
  - Collections store attachments alongside JSON documents

PREFERENCES:
  - Validate JSON structure at ingest; fail loudly on schema drift
  - Expose only the SQL endpoints the API consumer actually needs
  - Keep datasetd configuration in a versioned JSON file
  - Front end: semantic HTML, TypeScript strict mode, minimal deps

CONTEXT:
  (Describe your current project, collection schemas, API endpoints,
   or anything Harvey should keep in mind.)
